column1: Anar was one of the four Dwarves that accompanied Bilbo Baggins on his journeys after his birthday party.
In the early writings of the chapter "A Long-expected Party"
column2: Anar was given some dialogue and a bit more development.  However
column3: J.R.R. Tolkien later changed his mind
column4: and did not disclose his name in the book nor gave him any dialogue.

column3: is a dwarf from the Völuspá. His name most likely means "the Other" or "Starer".Chester Nathan Gould
